Line 1-3: Imports for file handling, UI components, and the message data model.
Line 5: Defines the MessageBubble as a stateless widget to display a single message entry.
Line 6: Holds the message data object passed via the constructor.
Line 11: Overrides the build method to define the bubble's appearance.
Line 12: Determines if the message was sent by the current user or received.
Line 13-14: Accesses the current theme for consistent coloring.
Line 16: Aligns the entire widget to the right for "sent" messages and left for "received" ones.
Line 18: Wraps the bubble and metadata in a Column.
Line 21-43: The main bubble container with dynamic margins, padding, and background color based on message type.
Line 30-35: Configures asymmetric border radii to create the distinct "bubble" shape.
Line 44: Logic to decide what content to show inside the bubble.
Line 45-51: If the message has decrypted text, it displays a Text widget with appropriate contrasting colors.
Line 52-78: If the message points to an image path, it displays the image with a corner lock icon for sent messages (visual indicator of stego).
Line 79-96: Fallback UI shown if neither text nor image path is available, indicating the presence of raw encrypted data.
Line 98-107: A small metadata label below the bubble indicating "Sent" or "Received".
